OVERVIEW\
\
This sample shows how to use the QTMovie frameImageAtTime: method to get an NSImage for the frame at a given time in a QTMovie.\
\
Mac OS X Leopard contains a new version of this method that gives the ability to pass a dictionary of attributes describing exactly the kind of image you want as shown here:\
\
- (NSImage *)frameImageAtTime:(QTTime)time\
